sentence: Looking at options trading activity among components of the Russell 3000 index, there is noteworthy activity today in Cal-Maine Foods Inc (Symbol: CALM), where a total volume of 2,469 contracts has been traded thus far today, a contract volume which is representative of approximately 246,900 underlying shares (given that every 1 contract represents 100 underlying shares).
That number works out to 41.9% of CALM's average daily trading volume over the past month, of 588,790 shares.
Especially high volume was seen for the $50 strike call option expiring November 18, 2016 , with 563 contracts trading so far today, representing approximately 56,300 underlying shares of CALM.

Salesforce.com Inc (Symbol: CRM) saw options trading volume of 28,891 contracts, representing approximately 2.9 million underlying shares or approximately 40.7% of CRM's average daily trading volume over the past month, of 7.1 million shares.
Particularly high volume was seen for the $65 strike put option expiring November 18, 2016 , with 2,535 contracts trading so far today, representing approximately 253,500 underlying shares of CRM.
